03 月 12 日','<p>工程主要包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>在水邊圍及馬田村建洪氾抽水站，並包括內部和外部裝飾以及相關的蓄洪池</li><li>在水邊圍建邊界牆包括圍欄和閘口</li><li>在馬田村建擋土牆包括圍欄和閘口</li><li>渠務工程，電纜管道及兩個抽水站相關的拉線井</li><li>在水邊圍及馬田村的園林綠化工程</li><li>在流浮山道十字路口排水道和近屏山近新慶村建矩形排水渠道</li><li>其他上述項目的輔助工程</li><li>鋪設永寧圍附近的建築排水渠</li><li>鋪設直徑 1200毫米的雙管式水道及相關的排水口和特殊沙井</li></ul>'),(226,'lmdmbo7mcxhr75mi86wqonc1','落馬洲過關邊界第一期 - 收費亭擴建及其它設施','2025-06-03 01:56:56.050000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.300000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','落馬洲過關邊界第一期 - 收費亭擴建及其它設施','建築署','1999 年 03 月 01 日 - 1999 年 12 月 31 日','<p>這是一項快速工程。於落馬洲興建一大型過境交通平臺。合約包括設計和建造地基系統、過境站、鋼結構牌樓及其他配合設施。</p><br/><p>繁忙的過境交通，爲儘快完成本專案帶來沈重的壓力。我司爲加速完成任務，作出重大努力，與各有關單位衷誠合作，終於得以最短的時間完成本專案。</p><br/><p>另一方面，在施工期間，儘量避免影響已經相當繁忙的過境交通，也帶來一定程度的挑戰。</p>'),(228,'edvzcsqgbv7215ih3rgl9qad','新界馬鞍山九十二區馬鞍山綜合運動場第一期建造工程 (合約編號：RE G324)','2025-06-03 01:59:31.072000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.352000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','新界馬鞍山九十二區馬鞍山綜合運動場第一期建造工程','建築署','1998 年 01 月 01 日 - 1999 年 08 月 27 日','<p>運動場包括跑道及足球場，總地盤面積約 42,000平方米。</p><br/><p>建造鋼筋混凝土看臺和鋼結構頂篷及鋼製覆蓋板。 打樁地基面積約長130米x 闊22 米，由頂篷最高點到地面約16.8米。</p><br/><p>第一期體育場館包括完成一個運動場和看臺。</p><br/><p>土壤，地表和地下排水。</p><br/><p>外部工程及附屬建築物。</p><br/><p>屋宇裝備安裝。</p><br/><br/><p>停車場，花槽，緊急車輛通道，鋪砌行人路面，圍牆，排水工程。</p>'),(230,'jmiobm7e5o7a4lwkk52zic8y','西北客運大樓及停機坪 (香港機場管理局 合約編號304)','2025-06-03 02:00:17.546000','2025-07-07 07:17:36.934000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','西北客運大樓及停機坪','香港機場管理局','1997 年 09 月 01 日 - 1999 年 12 月 31 日','<p>本專案包括建造香港國際機場之西北客運大樓，十一條連接橋及占地十萬平方呎之停機坪。爲順利完成本專案，承建商面對不同的挑戰。由於施工期間，需要確保機場的日常運作不受影響，承建商採取了嚴格的控制措施，包括管制工人及機械的活動範圍等，有效地控制及減低施工期間對機場的影響。除此之外，鋼結構組成的客運大樓屋頂也是一個很大的挑戰。由於本工程的西北客運大樓是以45度角與主客運大樓交接。因此，鋼結構屋頂形成了非常複雜的幾何設計，我們採用了先進的測量技術及相關的儀器，成功地完成了組裝的任務，確保工程的質量。在鋼結構的接駁方法上，我們選擇了縲絲接合的設計以取代焊接法。因此方法更能配合安裝現場的施工環境，減短安裝時間。另一方面，也消除了機管局對焊接法所産生的火花而導致影響機場運作的疑慮。</p>'),(232,'fodw4g1poot5qgpvhkhb21ag','九龍觀塘康寧道公園第一期建造工程 (合約編號：SS E362)','2025-06-03 02:01:26.345000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.643000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','九龍觀塘康寧道公園第一期建造工程','建築署','1997 年 04 月 11 日 - 1999 年 03 月 26 日','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>地盤平整工程包括大型挖掘約 60,000立方米，大約有 30％是岩層挖 掘。</li><li>建設長250米的護土牆，最高點為12米</li><li>在斜坡上興建一條長130米的行車天橋。</li><li>興建單幢式服務大樓（43mx12mx3.7m高）包括更衣室，廁所，售票 處，儲藏室，辦公室，急救室。職員室，機房，天井，憩坐處，小食亭 及通風廊。</li><li>外場工程包括圍牆，網球場，遊樂場，緩跑徑，健身站，觀景亭，泵房 和噴泉。</li><li>環境美化工程，停車場，公園家具，渠務和管道工程，機電工程，濾水 系統和水循環系統。</li></ul>'),(234,'nhnmbohfzybp2qsuveiyghxy','大嶼山及機場鐵路九龍南隧道及輔助樓房 (合約編號：503B)','2025-06-03 02:03:53.695000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.233000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','大嶼山及機場鐵路九龍南隧道及輔助樓房','香港鐵路有限公司','1994 年 11 月 01 日 - 1998 年 02 月 28 日','<p>這工程是機場快線的其中一段，工程包括在西九沉管式隧道和新九龍站之間建造機房大樓及隧道。</p><br/><p>工程項目包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造截水牆</li><li>大型開挖作隧道興建</li><li>鑽孔樁工程</li><li>安裝防洪閘和在水底安裝海水引進 /出PC裝置</li><li>相關的渠務及路面配套</li><li>附屬建築物</li><li>裝飾面及面板</li><li>環境美化</li></ul>'),(236,'yk6d40bs16eemftm7go9mt0t','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline (Contract No. DC/2003/01)','2025-06-03 02:08:55.365000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.697000',NULL,8,36,'en','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','<p>Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.</p><br/><p>The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.</p>'),(238,'otszagaypmvr5lyfysjgummb','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II (Contract No. DC/2001/01)','2025-06-03 02:09:49.655000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.374000',NULL,8,36,'en','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II','Sewerage Projects Division','08 March 2002 - 18 October 2005','<p>The major element of works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 primary sedimentation tanks and the associated primary sludge pumping station with a total footprint of 5060m2</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 aeration tanks and the 2 associated aeration tank control rooms with a total footprint of 7690m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 drainage pumping station with a depth of approximately 8m.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 12 final sedimentation tanks with a total footprint of 7150m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 RAS pumping station with a footprint of 450m2, 2 grit classifiers, 2 flume channels and 1 aerated grit channel</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the chambers, ducts, pipes, channels, trenches, drawpits , scum pits, drains, road, air main, and painting works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of piled foundations including 400 nos. of 1m diameter bored piles and 878 nos. of 219mm diameter mini piles</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply and lay D.I. mild steel and precast concrete pipes with diameter ranging from 200mm to 1600mm, where the total length is approximately 1.5km</li></ul>'),(240,'lertqjjqqxy0og3atsb5s9vi','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai (Contract No. DC/2000/12)','2025-06-03 02:11:13.907000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.395000',NULL,8,36,'en','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai','Drainage Services Department','20 December 2001 - 12 March 2004','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen Floodwater Pumping Station on raft foundation including internal and external finishes and their associated floodwater storage ponds</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Boundary wall at Shui Pin Wai including fencing and gates</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Retaining walls at Ma Tin Tsuen including fencing and gates</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Drainage works, cable ducts and drawpits associated with the two pumping stations</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works at Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Cross road drain at Lau Fau Shan Road and rectangular drainage channels near San Hing Tsuen, Ping Shan</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Other ancillary works associated with items above</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of drainage channels near Wing Ning Wai</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the twin 1200mm diameter pipes and the associated outfall and special manhole</li></ul>'),(242,'to5e09w2hdoetoypsmapi4hz','Expansion of Kiosks and other Facilities at Lok Ma Chau Boundary Crossing, Phase I','2025-06-03 02:11:53.115000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.966000',NULL,8,36,'en','Expansion of Kiosks and other Facilities at Lok Ma Chau Boundary Crossing, Phase I','Architectural Services Department, HKSAR','01 March 1999 - 31 December 1999','<p>This is a fast track project for the construction of a large podium at Lok Ma Chau for the cross border traffic. The project included the design and construction of piled foundation systems and the podium, kiosks, structural steel roof canopies and the other associated facilities.</p><br/><p>The extremely busy cross border traffic has bring along immence pressures to the rapid completion of the project. In order to complete the project in the shortest possible time, the Group has deployed huge amount of resources and affort, worked with close co-operations with all concerned parties. Finally, the project was completed on time.</p><br/><p>On the other hands, to mitigate any impact on the extremely busy cross border traffic during the construction was another major challenge</p>'),(244,'xvjg8epm7rnzki88zcbgy9z1','Completion of Ma On Shan Sports Complex, Phase I at Area 92, Ma On Shan, N.T. (Contract No. RE G324)','2025-06-03 02:12:43.753000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.922000',NULL,8,36,'en','Completion of Ma On Shan Sports Complex, Phase I at Area 92, Ma On Shan, N.T.','Architectural Services Department Government of HKSAR','01 January 1998 - 27 August 1999','<p>A sports field, total site area approx. 42,000 m2 comprising running track, football field.</p><br/><p>Spectator stand with reinforced concrete structure and structural steel canopy with steel sheet cladding and piling foundations approx. 130m x 22m overall on plan and 16.8m high from ground level to the top of steel canopy.</p><br/><p>Completion of a partially completed sports complex comprising a sports field and a spectator stand.</p><br/><p>Soil, surface at er and sub-soil drainage.</p><br/><p>External works and ancillary buildings.</p><br/><p>Building services installation.</p><br/><p>Car park, planter, Emergency Vehicular Access (EVA), paving, fence wall, drainage works</p>'),(246,'omfvvjmlh33o7ydl6arjlbb4','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works (AA Contract 304)','2025-06-03 02:13:26.937000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.556000',NULL,8,36,'en','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','01 September 1997 - 31 December 1999','<p>The contract to build the concourse extension, eleven fixed link bridges and 100,000ft². of apron area was awarded to the joint venture between Zen Pacific and Shui On. The project presented a number of challenges, not least the construction of the steel roof. The roof has a particularly complex geometry as the Northwest Concourse branches out from the main building at a 45-degree angle, which gives rise to grids of parallelograms with no right angles. A bolted design was chosen for the roof instead of the welded method used on the main terminal. The method of construction was chosen because it was more economical given the small number of roof modules involved and it improved installation time significantly. In addition, the method addressed the Airport Authority’s concerns over sparks from welding, which might have interfered with the airport’s operation.</p>'),(248,'uus4ub69gl1k57o97sl5anjt','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon (Contract No. SS E362)','2025-06-03 02:14:20.007000','2025-07-07 07:17:33.602000',NULL,8,36,'en','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','11 April 1997 - 26 March 1999','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The site formation includes a bulk excavation area of approximately 60,000m3. approximately 30% was rock excavation.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 250m long retaining walls with maximum height of 12m.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a 130m-long carriageway bridge on a slope.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a single storey service building (43mx12mx3.7m high) with changing rooms, toilets, booking office, storage room, general office, first aid room, staff room, plant rooms, open court, seating area, kiosk and breezeway.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>External works comprising barrier walls, tennis courts, play area, jogging tracks, fitness stations, pavilion, pump rooms and fountains.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works, car park, park furniture, drainage and plumbing works, M&amp;E works, water filtration and circulation installation.</li></ul>'),(250,'pvajhpcgk24obij1pybbjgpt','Lantau and Airport Railway Kowloon South Tunnels and Ancillary Building (MTRC Contract No.503B)','2025-06-03 02:15:14.387000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.270000',NULL,8,36,'en','Lantau and Airport Railway Kowloon South Tunnels and Ancillary Building','Mass Transit Railway Corporation','01 November 1994 - 28 February 1998','<p>This project, which forms part of the overall scheme for the Lantau and Airport Railway Link between the Western Immersed Tube and the new Kowloon Station, involves the construction of plant buildings and tunnels.</p><br/><p>The project consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of diaphragm walls</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Large open cut excavation to construct the tunnel sections</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Bored piling works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation of floodgates and positioning of seawater intake/outfall p c units underwater</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated drainage and access roads</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Ancillary building</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Architectural; finishes and cladding</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>landscaping</li></ul>'),(316,'tkmw8abovmw9wq5azjqe3bok','Contract No. SS J502 Construction of Animal Management and Animal Welfare Building Complex in Kai Tak Development','2025-06-02 07:59:27.890000','2025-07-07 07:17:17.974000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.221000',8,36,'en','Contract No. SS J502 Construction of Animal Management and Animal Welfare Building Complex in Kai Tak Development','Architectural Service Department','21 September 2020 - 29 February 2024','<p>Managed by Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department (AFCD), the Animal Management and Animal Welfare Building Complex in Kai Tak features about 270 animal-keeping facilities, more than double the capacity of the former site in To Kwa Wan. It includes enhanced quarantine options to reduce waiting times for imported animals.</p><p>This project comprises the construction of a 15-storey animal management and animal welfare building (overall height approximately 70m) and approximate construction floor area of 21,300m2 for re-provisioning of the required operational and supporting facilities for various AFCD divisions, including statutory quarantine centre for imported animals under the Rabies Ordinance (Cap. 421), library, classrooms, exhibition areas, animal rehome facilities for the promotion of animal welfare, laboratory facilities, offices, staff facilities, storage, car park areas, loading/unloading bays and other ancillary facilities.</p>'),(317,'fozqi98t6jr4tbri35j8uh0y','Main Contract Works for The Shaw Auditorium at The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology','2025-06-02 08:18:52.160000','2025-07-07 07:17:17.978000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.233000',8,36,'en','Main Contract Works for The Shaw Auditorium at The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology','The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (HKUST)','09 September 2019 - 08 November 2020','<p>The new Shaw Auditorium aspires to become a landmark at HKUST for large scale events including lectures, concerts, exhibitions, and ceremonies.  It aims to create a vibrant cultural scene enriching the lifestyle and learning experience for students, staff and alumni. The multi-purpose auditorium has distinguished green features including energy saving systems, a twin-tank design for potable water and flushing systems, and enhanced indoor air quality.</p><p>The project involves constructing a 3-storey building near the south entrance of HKUST, with a capacity to accommodate 1300 people. The construction work includes foundation, constructing reinforced concrete structure, building the envelope, and other building works.  Since the construction work took place on-campus, stringent and frequent noise and air quality control measures were implemented to mitigate the impact on university activities during the construction period.</p>'),(318,'f851dbwvzftmumjvq9o39zap','Main Contract Works for Lam Tsuen Farmland','2025-06-02 07:58:36.391000','2025-07-07 07:17:17.980000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.243000',8,36,'en','Main Contract Works for Lam Tsuen Farmland','City University of Hong Kong','14 December 2020 - 26 February 2022','<p>CityU has purchased a plot of farmland in Lam Tsuen, Tai Po, with an area of over 10,000 square metres to build a farm. The farm will house over 20 cows and will be used for educational purposes by the College of Veterinary Medicine and Life Sciences.</p><p>The works comprise the construction of 13 nos. of building including Adult Barn, Young Stock Barn, Main Building Block, Changing Room Block, Caretaker Quarters Block, Machine Store Block, Feed Centre Block, Transformer &amp; Generator Room Block, Fire Service, Sprinkler System &amp; Pump Room Block, Water Tank &amp; Pump Room, Storage Unit, Sewage Treatment Unit, Micro-Filtration Unit, site-wide underground drainage system, underground water pipes, underground cable draw pits, underground earthing and lightning system and associated E&amp;M systems, plus emergency vehicle access, fencing, entrance gate and landscaping works.</p>'),(319,'vypc85oomdply7vi2eaoerhj','Redevelopment of Island School, 20 Borrett Road, Mid-Levels, Hong Kong','2025-06-02 08:34:57.711000','2025-07-07 07:17:17.979000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.239000',8,36,'en','Redevelopment of Island School, 20 Borrett Road, Mid-Levels, Hong Kong','English Schools Foundation','14 December 2018 - 10 August 2022','<p>The ESF Island School is an international secondary school built in 1974. Faced with inadequate teaching space, concrete spalling, steel bar corrosion, and other structural issues that cannot be resolved by costly maintenance, ESF proposed redeveloping the aging school premises, which the Education Bureau (EDB) has agreed to in principle based on the existing conditions and ESF&#x27;s plans to improve the learning and teaching environment.</p><p>The project includes the construction of an 8-storey school premises with 42 classrooms. Inside the new facility, there will be 4 small group teaching rooms, 7 laboratories, 8 special rooms, a library, an indoor swimming pool, administration offices, and an auditorium designed with concert hall-quality acoustics.</p>'),(320,'gcejxftl2488v6axmfi2aj85','Contract No. NL/2020/01 Tung Chung New Town Extension - Community Liaison Centre','2025-06-02 07:36:05.961000','2025-07-07 07:17:17.974000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.261000',8,36,'en','Contract No. NL/2020/01 Tung Chung New Town Extension - Community Liaison Centre','Civil Engineering and Development Department','31 December 2020 - 07 July 2021','<p>The purpose of the works is remodeling the existing 2-storey Site Office of construction floor area (“CFA”) with approximate 3,000 sq.m. into a building compound to accommodate the satellite office of Sustainable Lantau Office (SLO) with its consultants’ project offices, exhibition and display gallery for CEDD Projects, and provide public gathering / meeting / event spaces for the local community and government officals to connect and communicate.</p><br/><p>A new Atrium space feature is introduced to the existing site office building by removing part of the floor slab and associated supporting structure of 1/F floor area. The atrium, surrounded on 3 sides by a new gallery of corridor with glass balustrades, opens to a new Grand Staircase as a multi-purpose space for public events. A new skylight is installed above  by demolishing part of the existing pitched roof while leaving the support structure intact. Structural strengthening work is adopted to ensure the stability of the existing building. Internal re-partitioning of and refurbishment of spaces of both floors are required to provide new office space and other ancillary facilities. Various installations of Building Services would be implemented according to architectural layout. Interior and semioutdoor landscaping features shall be carried out at specified locations.</p>'),(321,'fujms5aigjeqhyni3k7yrzhj','Construction of Two 30-classroom Primary Schools at Site 1A-3 and Site 1A-4, Kai Tak Development, Kowloon (Contract No. SS B507)','2025-06-02 09:38:56.802000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.157000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.379000',8,36,'en','Construction of Two 30-classroom Primary Schools at Site 1A-3 and Site 1A-4, Kai Tak Development, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','29 November 2013 - 31 December 2015','<p>Kai Tak Development is a huge and complicated development project spanning a total planning area of over 320 hectares. The proposal of Kai Tak Development consists of community, housing, business, tourism and infrastructural uses.</p><p>This is a community construction project which consists of the construction of two primary schools with an approximate site area of 13,200m2. The design of the school complements the concept of Kai Tak Development by including numerous environmental elements. The design also won the &quot;HKIA Merit Award of Hong Kong 2015 – Community Building&quot;. The external walls were installed with environmental wooden screens and metal screens to save the energy required by the air-conditioning system and also make the building become unique. The walls are made of Architectural concrete, creating a natural landscape and reducing the use of additional materials. In addition, gardens were set up in different locations and floors of the buildings and green roofs were set outside the library, providing students with a comfortable learning and reading environment.</p>'),(322,'wzjzf9qigd83og69sntsu6z6','The Management Contract for Proposed Development for Hang Seng Management College','2025-06-02 09:49:16.708000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.169000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.412000',8,36,'en','The Management Contract for Proposed Development for Hang Seng Management College','Hang Seng School of Commerce','07 October 2011 - 27 October 2015','<p>This contract is part of the development plan of Hang Seng Management College. It aims to expand a green campus which offers state-of-the-art learning, teaching, research and residential facilities to meet the needs and demands of quality tertiary education in the 21st century.</p><p>The construction comprises the proposed development at Block A, B, C, D and F for the Hang Seng Management College, which includes the S H Ho Academic Building, Sports and Amenities Centre, HSMC Plaza, Lee Quo Wei Academic Building, and HSMC Jockey Club Residential Colleges. Awarded by Hong Kong Green Building Council, the S H Ho Academic Building, Sports and Amenities Centre, Lee Quo Wei Academic Building and the student residence halls achieved Final Platinum rating in the BEAM Plus Assessment Scheme.</p>'),(323,'nypyym80vas83o17k4k22e1w','St. Paul\'s Hospital Redevelopment - Demolition of Existing Old Block and Structures, Construction of a New Basement and Extension of Block A, Alteration and Addition Works to Block A, Block B and Basement D','2025-06-02 08:40:33.122000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.177000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.690000',8,36,'en','St. Paul\'s Hospital Redevelopment - Demolition of Existing Old Block and Structures, Construction of a New Basement and Extension of Block A, Alteration and Addition Works to Block A, Block B and Basement D','The Mother Superior of the Soeurs De Saint Paul De Chartres (Hong Kong)','10 October 2017 - 25 September 2024','<p>St. Paul&#x27;s Hospital was founded in 1898 by the Sisters of St. Paul de Chartres. Located in the heart of Causeway Bay, this comprehensive, acute private hospital provides around 500 beds across over 20 departments, with ongoing redevelopment to expand its facilities and diversify services.</p><p>This project involves the construction of a new basement and extension of Block A, alteration and addition works to Blocks A, B, and Basement D, conversion of an open car park to a landscaped garden, road widening and paving works at Eastern Hospital Road, and the demolition of an existing old block followed by the construction of a new basement structure and superstructure.</p>'),(324,'r26mr9hpngfconrup9takv9m','Reprovisioning of New Territories South Animal Management Centre and Shatin Plant Quarantine Station (Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1113)','2025-06-02 09:47:32.517000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.212000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.748000',8,36,'en','Reprovisioning of New Territories South Animal Management Centre and Shatin Plant Quarantine Station','MTR Corporation Limited','10 September 2012 - 29 November 2013','<p>The Shatin to Central Line is one of the railway lines recommended by Hong Kong Government, with a series of stations strategically built along the railway. Due to the construction of Hin Keng Station, it was neccessary to reprovision the New Territories South Animal Management Centre and Shatin Plant Quarantine Station from Tai Wai Che Kung Miu Road and Hin Keng Street to other locations.</p><p>Our group was awarded this reprovisioning project which included the reprovisioning of the three-storey New Territories South Animal Management Centre and single-storey Shatin Plant Quarantine station. With good communication and understanding with the stakeholders throughout the project, we managed toobtain consensus on the work and carried out the project smoothly.</p>'),(325,'o6t1muznyvgo0nlp990by619','Contract No. SS H514 Construction of a 30-classroom Primary School at Shui Chuen O, Sha Tin','2025-06-02 08:08:33.776000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.219000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.762000',8,36,'en','Contract No. SS H514 Construction of a 30-classroom Primary School at Shui Chuen O, Sha Tin','Architectural Service Department','14 January 2020 - 22 June 2022','<p>Education Bureau addresses the projected demand for public sector primary school places in the Sha Tin District due to the population growth in the area brought by the moving in of Shui Chuen O Estate, the construction of a primary school at Shui Chuen O, Sha Tin is imperative.</p><p>The works include the construction of a 30-classroom primary school comprising a 7-storey classroom block (with overall height of approximately 32 metres), a 6-storey special room-cum-assembly hall block (with overall height of approximately 23 metres) and associated facilities together with geotechnical works of slope treatment, drainage and external works. The classroom block and the special room-cum assembly hall block are linked by an elevated link bridge. The construction floor area is approximately 11,000 m2.</p>'),(326,'o2b3gcl6ket6jpt6hbapn49w','Conversion of the Secondary Pool of the Lai Chi Kok Park Swimming Pool into an Indoor Heated Pool (Contract No. AL W316)','2025-06-02 09:59:20.266000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.933000','2025-07-07 07:17:19.389000',8,36,'en','Conversion of the Secondary Pool of the Lai Chi Kok Park Swimming Pool into an Indoor Heated Pool','Architectural Services Department','01 February 2010 - 31 March 2012','<p>Hong Kong Government proposed to build an indoor heated swimming pool, which would have the effect of promoting swimming in winter and better health amongst the residents in the district, and thus enhancing the overall usage of the swimming pool.</p><p>The project includes the provision of a light cover and retractable sidewalls for the secondary pool; a new heating system to the secondary pool and a covered-walkway; demolition of the existing children&#x27;s fun pool and associated improvements to ventilation and hot water systems in changing room.</p>'),(327,'ek0fw6kv4p2vfs0k19biizxd','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','2025-06-02 09:29:30.302000','2025-07-07 07:17:19.127000','2025-07-07 07:17:19.442000',8,36,'en','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University','15 June 2015 - 29 August 2019','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the design and construction of a footbridge linking the Main Campus and the Phase 8 development of The Hong Kong Polytechnic University. The footbridge is designed as a steel bow-string arch structure with a main span length of 68m across the entire Chatham Road South. The pedestrian walkway with an overall width of about 7m and its associated sub-structures are hung from the two main arch beams by high-tensioned steel bar. The aesthetic form of the footbridge is designed according to the concept of &quot;Flying Fish&quot; and echoes with the surrounding iconic buildings of the University.</p><p>The works under the project include the design and construction of pile foundation, pile cap, RC lift shaft structures, lift installation, steel footbridge structure and its associated sub- structures, architectural works and finishes, building services works, footbridge connection works involving alternation and addition works to the existing Block Z at Phase 8 development.</p>'),(328,'rq9404olbhb3qa2n84beiah5','New Midfield Screening Building (Contract P531)','2025-06-02 09:56:18.264000','2025-07-07 07:17:18.956000','2025-07-07 07:17:19.477000',8,36,'en','New Midfield Screening Building','Airport Authority Hong Kong','19 July 2011 - 03 September 2012','<p>In order to increase the capacity of Hong Kong International Airport to handle passenger and cargo transport, the Airport Authority has issued a Midfield development project to enhance Hong Kong&#x27;s competitiveness in the international transport industry and enable Hong Kong International Airport to continue serving as a regional and regional aviation hub for Asia and the world.</p><p>Our group was awarded one of the ancillary works under the Midfield Development Plan, a Design and Build project including design, supply, construction, testing and commissioning of the New Midfield Screening Building.</p>'),(329,'xgrp0qd3f2c116k4y0gii30i','Contract No. SS C503 Design and Construction of Kowloon East Regional Headquarters and Operational Base cum Ngau Tau Kok Divisional Police Station at 105 Concorde Road, Kai Tak','2025-06-02 09:10:38.905000','2025-07-07 07:17:19.407000','2025-07-07 07:17:20.481000',8,36,'en','Contract No. SS C503 Design and Construction of Kowloon East Regional Headquarters and Operational Base cum Ngau Tau Kok Divisional Police Station at 105 Concorde Road, Kai Tak','Architectural Services Department','11 July 2016 - 05 March 2020','<p>The scope of works of the contract consists of the demolition of the decommissioned 10-storey Hong Kong Police Force Kai Tak Operational Base building; design and construction of about 17 storeys integrated complex for the new Kowloon East Police Regional Headquarters and Operational Base cum Ngau Tau Kok Divisional Police Station with carparking floors, together with associated building services installations, external works and drainage. The net operational floor area is approximately 20,690 square metres. The site area is approximately 6,600 square metres.</p>'),(330,'l1u5nwq5i6zasui2454eg1of','The Construction of an 18-Classroom Primary School at Tai Pak Tin Street, Kwai Chung (Contract No. SS R323)','2025-06-02 11:11:24.572000','2025-07-07 07:17:19.442000','2025-07-07 07:17:20.516000',8,36,'en','The Construction of an 18-Classroom Primary School at Tai Pak Tin Street, Kwai Chung','Architectural Services Department','30 April 2007 - 31 July 2009','<p>The Contract consists of the construction of a primary school with 18 classrooms comprising a 10-storey school block including an assembly hall (overall height 39.50 metres) with pile foundations, associated facilities, drainage and external works. The construction floor area of school building is approx. 8,550 m2.</p>'),(331,'iyn151ztr7j2elw06vl1jkby','Thrill Mountain & Polar Adventure (Ocean Park Master Redevelopment Project Contract No. CS03)','2025-06-02 10:01:49.373000','2025-07-07 07:17:20.462000','2025-07-07 07:17:20.671000',8,36,'en','Thrill Mountain & Polar Adventure','Ocean Park Corporation','02 November 2009 - 08 July 2012','<p>Ocean Park&#x27;s Master Redevelopment Plan included two new themed projects in &quot;The Summit&quot; area - &quot;Thrill Mountain&quot; and &quot;Polar Adventure&quot;, covering a total area of 400,000 square feet.</p><p>&quot;Thrill Mountain&quot; offered six attractions, booth games, as well as food, beverages and merchandise, while &quot;Polar Adventure&quot; consists of &quot;North Pole Encounter&quot;, &quot;South Pole Spectacular&quot; and &quot;Arctic Blast &quot;.</p><p>Several building materials used in the construction included fiberglass reinforced concrete for the manufacture of icebergs and imitation stones. In order to allow visitors to have the best underwater experience, the exhibition hall used transparent acrylic plates and transparent tempered glass of 202mm thickness for the construction of underwater tunnels and underwater screen. The newly opened restaurant also used transparent acrylic panel for the screen, allowing visitors to watch the Antarctic penguins while enjoying their food.</p>'),(332,'uregwx9f4vjtu4ht844u08k8','The Proposed Alteration and Addition Works for Little Dalton School at 1/F & 2/F Imperial Cullinan, No. 10 Hoi Fai Road, Tai Kok Tsui, Kowloon','2025-06-02 09:04:07.762000','2025-07-07 07:17:20.584000','2025-07-07 07:17:21.447000',8,36,'en','The Proposed Alteration and Addition Works for Little Dalton School at 1/F & 2/F Imperial Cullinan, No. 10 Hoi Fai Road, Tai Kok Tsui, Kowloon','Dalton Foundation Limited','18 December 2016 - 16 June 2017','<p>The Dalton School of Hong Kong is a non-profit bilingual (Mandarin, English) kindergarten and primary school that combines the wisdom of traditional Chinese culture with the world-renowned Dalton Education Program. The school aims to provide a joyful environment that will nurture children&#x27;s inquisitiveness; develop their confidence in their ability to succeed; exploit their natural ability to acquire languages; and educate them to become happy, responsible and independent learners and thinkers.</p><p>The project involves demolition works of existing blockwall partition, installation of new blockwall, dry wall and glass partitions, timber door finishings, glass doors, painting works, brand new vinyl flooring and E&amp;M installation works within a very tight construction timeline.</p>'),(333,'ry8gjk8ct81awgkz4synds1t','Main Contract works for Malvern College Hong Kong Campus at Area 4, Fo Chun Road, Tai Po','2025-06-02 08:58:27.864000','2025-07-07 07:17:21.385000','2025-07-07 07:17:21.896000',8,36,'en','Main Contract works for Malvern College Hong Kong Campus at Area 4, Fo Chun Road, Tai Po','Malvern College Hong Kong Limited','27 January 2017 - 24 August 2018','<p>For international city like Hong Kong, it is important to have a vibrant international school sector to meet the needs of the city&#x27;s large and growing global community. With land supply shortage in Hong Kong, the Government therefore takes a facilitating role in growing the international school sector and introduced the School Allocation Exercise. Under this policy, Malvern College Hong Kong (MCHK) was awarded a greenfield site adjacent to the Hong Kong Science Park and the scenic Tolo Harbour, which is an extraordinary location. The construction of the school building was approved by the Education Bureau of the HKSAR in May 2015 and was opened in August 2018. It provides 960 places for both primary and secondary students from diverse cultural and educational backgrounds.</p><p>Malvern College Hong Kong is a 258,000 sqft, 7-storey, state-of-the-art campus comprising academic, sporting and recreational spaces. It incorporates the latest innovations and technologies in teaching, learning and environmental sustainability. The major scope of this project comprises the construction of a 6-lane &amp; 25m heated indoor pool, the AstroTurf Skypitch, a 450-seats auditorium, an open-plan library, seven science labs, a multi-purpose indoor sports hall, music rooms and a dining hall. It also provides beautiful landscaping and top roof with external sport playground.</p><p>The school offers a pleasant &amp; spacious environment for study.</p>'),(334,'eq8fo6b8x63eqprh3fv8maep','10-22 Mui Fong Street and 15-19 Kwai Heung Street, Sai Ying Pun for Student Residences for The University of Hong Kong','2025-06-02 08:21:41.502000','2025-07-07 07:17:21.419000','2025-07-07 07:17:22.061000',8,36,'en','10-22 Mui Fong Street and 15-19 Kwai Heung Street, Sai Ying Pun for Student Residences for The University of Hong Kong','The University of Hong Kong','02 April 2019 - 30 June 2022','<p>In July 2018, the Legislative Council (LegCo) Finance Committee (FC) approved a one-off grant for establishing the Higher Education Development Fund (HDF) to expedite the development of student hostels for six University Grants Committee (UGC)-funded universities that were facing shortfalls in hostel places, and The University of Hong Kong (HKU) is one of them.</p><p>On this project for HKU, a multi-storey tower was constructed, providing around 250 student hostel places including 2 storeys of public toilet, 6 nos. of accessible student rooms above podium level. Hostels facilities include common area, management staff accommodation and podium garden and provision of new temporary portable public toilet with related drainage at Mui Fong Street Sitting Out Area.</p>'),(335,'m4583w76qngi046x99n7b19p','Construction of Sewers, Rising Mains and Sewage Pumping Stations at Kam Tin, Nam Sang Wai and Au Tau in Yuen Long (Contract No. DC/2005/02)','2025-06-02 11:35:55.339000','2025-07-07 07:17:21.478000','2025-07-07 07:17:22.193000',8,36,'en','Construction of Sewers, Rising Mains and Sewage Pumping Stations at Kam Tin, Nam Sang Wai and Au Tau in Yuen Long','Drainage Services Department','29 December 2005 - 30 June 2010','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of Kam Tin Sewage Pumping Station, Shad Po Sewage Pumping Station and Nam Sang Wai Sewage Pumping Station</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of app. 6.6 km long sewers of dial. Ranging from 300 to 1200mm at Kam Tin and Nam Sang Wai of which app. 0.9 km long sewers to be laid by trench less technique</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of app. 5.7 km long twin rising mains of dial. Ranging from 250 to 900mm at Kam Tin and Nam Sang Wai of which app. 0.9 km long twin rising mains to be laid by trench less technique</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of app. 0.9 km long sewers of dial. Ranging from 300 to 900mm at Au Tau of which app. 0.2 km long sewers to be laid by trench less technique</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works associated with Kam Tin Sewage Pumping Station, Shad Po Sewage Pumping Station and Nam Sang Way Sewage Pumping Station</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Preservation and protection of trees within the site, tree felling and transplantation work associated with the construction of sewage pumping stations, and sewer and rising mains laying works; and</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Any other ancillary works associated with items above including manholes, chambers, road works, foot ways, fences, gates and the like.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply and installation of electrical and mechanical equipment for Kam Tin Sewage Pumping Station, Shad Po Sewage Pumping Station and Nam Sang Wai Sewage Pumping Station will be executed under separate concurrent E&amp;M contract</li></ul>'),(336,'ychu8zy0rlnkpwgzzgif1v8u','Reprovisioning of Harbour Road Sports Centre and Wan Chai Swimming Pool (Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1126)','2025-06-02 09:35:02.282000','2025-07-07 07:17:21.456000','2025-07-07 07:17:22.580000',8,36,'en','Reprovisioning of Harbour Road Sports Centre and Wan Chai Swimming Pool','MTR Corporation Limited','20 January 2014 - 31 May 2017','<p>Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a 17km-long railway line expansion undertaken by MTR Corporation in Kowloon and Hong Kong Island. The project involves stretching the line from Tai Wai to Hung Hom and Hung Hom to Admiralty sections, linking a number of existing railway lines passing through several districts in Hong Kong</p><p>The SCL Exhibition Station is located under the existing Wan Chai Ferry Pier Public Transport Interchange, Harbour Road Sports Centre (HRSC) and Wan Chai Swimming Pool (WCSP). As the station were to be constructed using the cut-and-cover method, the HRSC and WCSP had to be permanently relocated to the old public car park in the south. The existing facilities were demolished only after the reprovisioning work is completed.</p><p>The scope of the project comprised the construction of the new HRSC and WCSP, a 5-storey RC building with steel trussed roof. Associated with the new building, the scope is also included the design and construction of the external building envelope; design and construction of internal fabric and finishes, equipment and fittings; design and construction of building services works, including, among others, hoisting beams and support details, steelwork access platforms, electrical, ELV, filtration, ACMV, FS, lift &amp; escalator, Town Gas and plumbing and drainage systems.</p>'),(337,'zajkaiyq3oowk0gedpo3ym15','Redevelopment of Disciplined Services Quarters in Fu Tei, Tuen Mun (Contract No. SS A511)','2025-06-02 09:43:22.019000','2025-07-07 07:17:21.752000','2025-07-07 07:17:23.053000',8,36,'en','Redevelopment of Disciplined Services Quarters in Fu Tei, Tuen Mun','Architectural Services Department','18 December 2012 - 14 July 2015','<p>In order to alleviate the shortage of departmental quarters for disciplined services staff, it was proposed to develop the project site in Fu Tei, Tuen Mun into a new departmental quarter.</p><p>Our group was awarded this project and the works include the construction of a 20-storey building block housing 140 quarter unit. The main building contains management office, game centre and other facilities for residents. The main building is connected to the podium floor and garden with a carpark, transformer room, generator room and other facilities. A 11m high noise-barrier was placed at the west of the building to reduce the noise level of the quarters.</p>'),(338,'ddbetwex27d48ihm4gpxs4bn','Main Contract Works for Scout Association of Hong Kong at I.L. No. 8261, 34 Oi Kwan Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong','2025-06-02 09:06:13.281000','2025-07-07 07:17:21.894000','2025-07-07 07:17:23.766000',8,36,'en','Main Contract Works for Scout Association of Hong Kong at I.L. No. 8261, 34 Oi Kwan Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong','Scout Association of Hong Kong','18 July 2016 - 16 October 2018','<p>The Scout Association of Hong Kong formally inaugurated its centennial building on 20 April 2018 and is officially named as the &quot;Hong Kong Scout Centennial Building&quot;. This 21-storey building was redeveloped from the former 5-storey Tang Shiu-kin Building which served as the association&#x27;s Regional Headquarters for the Hong Kong Island Region. The towering structure marks a significant milestone in the continuous development of the scout history in the city.</p><p>The Hong Kong Scout Centennial Building incorporates many sustainable building designs, including sun shading fins to reduce energy penetration and natural ventilation for the staircase and lift lobbies. The building accommodates an Integrated Training Centre, Aviation Training Centre, a Performing Arts Centre and an Art Gallery, as well as logistic facilities such as Scout Shop, Scout Library and Multi-purpose Hall.</p><p>The scope of the HKSCB includes construction of reinforced concrete construction completed with all building services</p><p>With the establishment of the new building, the Scout Association of Hong Kong hopes to provide better venues and facilities for scout trainings in the city.</p>'),(339,'cadp586a5999pq89227ceapp','The Chinese University of Hong Kong – New Chapel to Theology Building','2025-06-02 10:07:45.942000','2025-07-07 07:17:22.066000','2025-07-07 07:17:26.692000',8,36,'en','The Chinese University of Hong Kong – New Chapel to Theology Building','The Chinese University of Hong Kong','02 October 2009 - 09 December 2011','<p>In order to provide a better environment for the student to have a devotional worship, The Chinese University of Hong Kong decided to build a new chapel.</p><p>Our group has awarded this New Chapel to Theology Building contract. The works consist of the construction of a 1,450 m2 chapel, where for accommodating 350 people. With its eastern style green glazed tiles roof, the new chapel assimilates into the natural environment. The round-shaped chapel is surrounded by windows to maximize natural light, it can save more energy and provide a nature view for the worship. The chapel also installed fourteen stained glass windows and is supported by 12 pillars with an emblem for one of the 12 disciples on each pillar.</p>'),(340,'fpujj9bs27owv0a1y7484zjy','Construction of Special School at Cornwall Street, Sham Shui Po, for Severely Intellectually Disable Children, Hong Kong (Contract No. SS S303)','2025-06-02 10:09:34.397000','2025-07-07 07:17:22.189000','2025-07-07 07:17:26.907000',8,36,'en','Construction of Special School at Cornwall Street, Sham Shui Po, for Severely Intellectually Disable Children, Hong Kong','Architectural Services Department','06 August 2007 - 10 July 2009','<p>The project consists of the construction of a 5-storey special school with boarding facility for severely intellectually disabled children (overall height of school block is 16.5 metres) with pile foundations, associated facilities, drainage and external works. The construction floor area of the school is approximately 8,320 square metres.</p>'),(341,'xa3v0zttn3854xja1h2qpn74','Vet Hospital (Ocean Park Master Redevelopment Project Contract CS01)','2025-06-02 11:13:44.579000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.248000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.594000',8,36,'en','Vet Hospital','Ocean Park Corporation','26 March 2007 - 31 October 2008','<p>The mojar element of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the structure of the Veterinary Hospital including the Pool Block, Office Block &amp; Transformer Room</li><li>Installation of architectural, E&amp;M, BS, Fire Services, Lift, MVAC &amp; the likes within the building of the Veterinary Hospital</li><li>Installation of utility services to the new Veterinary Hospital including Fresh water, salt water, fire services water, control cables</li><li>Construction of drainage &amp; sewerage system for discharging storm water &amp; foul water to the existing system in the vicinity</li><li>Installation, testing &amp; commissioning of a Life Support System at the Veterinary Hospital</li><li>Transportation of facilities &amp; equipments from the existing Veterinary Hospital to the new Veterinary Hospital upon occupation</li></ul>'),(342,'bvhriml4z5ppajtmjnamoxzy','Proposed Tseung Kwan O Joint Student Hostel The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and The Hong Kong Baptist University','2025-06-02 09:39:46.927000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.452000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.677000',8,36,'en','Proposed Tseung Kwan O Joint Student Hostel The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and The Hong Kong Baptist University','The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology','28 December 2012 - 02 June 2016','<p>To cater for the additional demand for student hostel places arising from the implementation of the four-year undergraduate curriculum and the further development of Hong Kong as a regional education hub, a number of University Grants Committee (UGC)-funded institutions are actively planning student hostel development projects, and the Tseung Kwan O Joint Student Hostel The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and The Hong Kong Baptist University is one of these developments.</p><p>This 520-place student hostel is a 9 floor building with living accommodation facilities (bedrooms, dining rooms etc) and  common facilities (multi-purpose room &amp; kitchen, study room, gym room, laundry etc.) .  The Sky Garden at the 5th Floor offers a pleasant environment for leisure.</p>'),(343,'jzctcimpsf8t00gy89veokbn','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Main Contract for the construction of the Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Hangar 2','2025-06-02 11:14:36.910000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.467000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.705000',8,36,'en','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Main Contract for the construction of the Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Hangar 2','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd.','14 November 2006 - 15 August 2007','<p>Major works consist of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of an air-craft hanger building including foundations, structural steel roof and superstructure, wall and roof claddings, supply and install M&amp;E equipment and Building Services.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a single storey ancillary office building with RC structure including the associated architectural finishes, M&amp; E and Building Services.</li></ul>'),(344,'t6d6dna3zj3b7l26cp4z7tos','香港科技大学逸夫演艺中心建设工程','2025-06-02 08:14:54.453000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.537000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.719000',8,36,'zh-CN','香港科技大学逸夫演艺中心建设工程','香港科技大学','2019 年 09 月 09 日 - 2020 年 11 月 08 日','<p>全新的逸夫演艺中心旨在成为香港科技大学的地标，举办大型活动，包括讲座、音乐会、展览和典礼，在校园内营造活力的文化氛围，丰富学生、教职员和校友的生活和学习体验。这座多功能会堂具有出色的环保设计，包括节能系统、可饮用水和冲厕系统的双水箱设计，以及提升室内空气质量等特点。</p><p>本工程项目涉及在西贡科大南边入口附近建造一座楼高3层且能容纳1300人的演艺中心。建造工程包括地基工程、建造钢筋混凝土结构、围护结构以及其他楼宇工程。由于施工在校园内进行，为减低施工期间对大学活动的影响，我们採取了严格和频密的噪音及空气质素管制措施。</p>'),(345,'iuj5v1kr47q4deq2meprt0vc','Contract No. SS G511 Construction of Columbarium at Cape Collinson Road in Chai Wan','2025-06-02 08:35:59.123000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.491000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.724000',8,36,'en','Contract No. SS G511 Construction of Columbarium at Cape Collinson Road in Chai Wan','Architectural Services Department','29 November 2018 - 31 August 2023','<p>To meet the increasing cremation needs of Hong Kong&#x27;s aging population, the government plans to complete the building of a 25,000-niche columbarium at Cape Collinson Road by 2022, with a pedestrian access route and road widening, as part of a broader policy to develop public columbarium facilities across the 18 districts.</p><p>The project includes the construction of a 5-storey building with around 25,000 niches, along with supporting facilities such as communal incense holders, eco-friendly joss paper burning facilities, passenger lifts, administrative offices, and digital kiosks. Additionally, the project involves building a pedestrian access route with escalators and stairs connecting Cape Collinson Road and San Ha Street, as well as road widening and improvement works on Cape Collinson Road.</p>'),(346,'tkvnvqp75lixqq3w7xal4uyq','合約編號 SS H514 沙田水泉澳一所設有三十間課室的小學','2025-06-02 07:56:33.453000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.505000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.729000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','合約編號 SS H514 沙田水泉澳一所設有三十間課室的小學','建築署','2020 年 01 月 14 日 - 2022 年 06 月 22 日','<p>教育局考慮到沙田區公營小學學位的預計需求，包括水泉澳邨入伙所帶來的區內人口增長，所以於水泉澳增設1所設有30間課室的全新資助小學。</p><p>本合約工程包括興建1所設有30間課室的小學，包括1座7層高的教學大樓（大約總高度 32 米）、1座6層高的特別室暨禮堂大樓（大約總高度 23 米）和相關設施，以及進行斜坡土力工程、渠務和外部工程。而教學大樓與特別室暨禮堂大樓則由一條高架橋連接。建築面積約為11,000平方米。</p><br/><br/>'),(347,'p4md0ppxelxfcf4pb5gqgt5p','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38 (Contract No. EP/SP/52/06)','2025-06-02 11:34:30.728000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.584000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.933000',8,36,'en','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38','Environmental Protection Department','03 July 2006 - 01 January 2010','<p>The EcoPark is a key element of the strategy that aims to promote the local recycling industry and jump-start a sustainable economy by providing long-term land facility for the environmental and recycling industry. By encouraging and promoting the reuse, recovery and recycling of our waste resources and return them to the consumption loop, the EcoPark will help capitalize the potential of the local recycling industry and alleviate the heavy demand of the Hong Kong landfills.</p><br/><p>EcoPark occupies 20 hectares of land in Tuen Mun Area 38 and will be developed in two phases. Phase I of EcoPark (about 8 ha) will be available for occupation towards the end of 2006 and Phase II (about 12 ha) in 2009. Various environmentally friendly features are being used for the first time in Hong Kong, such as the Sun Pipe, Solar power water faucet, and a Green roof just to name a few.</p>'),(348,'fodw4g1poot5qgpvhkhb21ag','九龍觀塘康寧道公園第一期建造工程 (合約編號：SS E362)','2025-06-03 02:01:26.345000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.643000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.943000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','九龍觀塘康寧道公園第一期建造工程','建築署','1997 年 04 月 11 日 - 1999 年 03 月 26 日','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>地盤平整工程包括大型挖掘約 60,000立方米，大約有 30％是岩層挖 掘。</li><li>建設長250米的護土牆，最高點為12米</li><li>在斜坡上興建一條長130米的行車天橋。</li><li>興建單幢式服務大樓（43mx12mx3.7m高）包括更衣室，廁所，售票 處，儲藏室，辦公室，急救室。職員室，機房，天井，憩坐處，小食亭 及通風廊。</li><li>外場工程包括圍牆，網球場，遊樂場，緩跑徑，健身站，觀景亭，泵房 和噴泉。</li><li>環境美化工程，停車場，公園家具，渠務和管道工程，機電工程，濾水 系統和水循環系統。</li></ul>'),(349,'jier9cr6ckcnuy8atrsdwsz7','漁農自然護理署新界南動物管理中心及沙田植物檢疫站重置工程 (沙田至中環線建造合約編號1113)','2025-06-02 09:46:01.506000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.642000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.026000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','漁農自然護理署新界南動物管理中心及沙田植物檢疫站重置工程','香港鐵路有限公司','2012 年 09 月 10 日 - 2013 年 11 月 29 日','<p>沙中綫是政府建議興建的其中一條策略性鐵路，該路線沿途將會興建一系列車站。其中因應顯徑站建造工程而須將原有於大圍車公廟路顯徑邨側的漁農自然護理署新界南動物管理中心和沙田植物檢疫站重置。</p><p>集團獲得這個重置項目，工程包括重置三層高的新界南動物管理中心，兩層高的沙田植物檢疫站及一層高的設備室等。過程中與持分者有著良好的溝通和瞭解，並預早取得工作上的共識，促成工程順利進行。</p>'),(350,'yk6d40bs16eemftm7go9mt0t','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline (Contract No. DC/2003/01)','2025-06-03 02:08:55.365000','2025-07-07 07:17:28.697000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.245000',8,36,'en','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','<p>Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.</p><br/><p>The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.</p>'),(351,'wyly6f50y7migxo4mcqt94un','HAECO Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 2 Main Contract Works','2025-06-02 11:37:18.462000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.328000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.565000',8,36,'en','HAECO Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 2 Main Contract Works','Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering Co., Ltd.','10 November 2005 - 20 December 2006','<p>The construction of the Hangar No. 2 will provide the Client with a new facility in excess of 14,000m2 in area which will be able to accommodate two + one wide-bodied aircraft at one time and will have the capability to undertake all maintenance and modification work currently handled at HKIA including but not limited to: heavy maintenance, modification, repair and overhaul of commercial aircraft and their components.</p><br/><p>The new steel hangar including foundation measured 170mx85m (14,450m2) on plan and is located to the east of the existing Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 1 facing the South Runway. The minimum clear span and headroom of the hangar required are 157m (wide) and 27m (high) respectively.</p>'),(352,'rjevkoaxttxsnpv51z1581iq','合约编号SS J502 渔农自然护理署动物管理及动物福利综合大楼的建造工程','2025-06-02 08:01:37.445000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.409000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.600000',8,36,'zh-CN','合约编号SS J502 渔农自然护理署动物管理及动物福利综合大楼的建造工程','建筑署','2020 年 09 月 21 日 - 2024 年 02 月 29 日','<p>由渔农自然护理署(渔护署)管理的动物管理及动物福利综合大楼拥有约270个动物暂住设施，容量是土瓜湾旧址的两倍多。该大楼拥有更妥善的检疫措施，以缩短进口动物的等待时间。</p><p>本项目旨在兴建一幢15层高的动物管理及动物福利综合大楼(总高度约70米)，建筑面积约21,300平方米，以重置渔护署各部门所需的营运和辅助设施，包括根据《狂犬病条例》(第421章)为进口动物设立的法定检疫中心、图书馆、课室、展览区、动物领养设施以促进动物福祉、实验室设施、办公室、员工设施、储存空间、停车场区域、装卸区及其他附属设施。</p>'),(353,'otszagaypmvr5lyfysjgummb','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II (Contract No. DC/2001/01)','2025-06-03 02:09:49.655000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.374000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.617000',8,36,'en','Construction of Shatin Sewage Treatment Works Stage III Extenstion Phase II','Sewerage Projects Division','08 March 2002 - 18 October 2005','<p>The major element of works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 primary sedimentation tanks and the associated primary sludge pumping station with a total footprint of 5060m2</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 6 aeration tanks and the 2 associated aeration tank control rooms with a total footprint of 7690m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 drainage pumping station with a depth of approximately 8m.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 12 final sedimentation tanks with a total footprint of 7150m2.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 1 RAS pumping station with a footprint of 450m2, 2 grit classifiers, 2 flume channels and 1 aerated grit channel</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the chambers, ducts, pipes, channels, trenches, drawpits , scum pits, drains, road, air main, and painting works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of piled foundations including 400 nos. of 1m diameter bored piles and 878 nos. of 219mm diameter mini piles</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supply and lay D.I. mild steel and precast concrete pipes with diameter ranging from 200mm to 1600mm, where the total length is approximately 1.5km</li></ul>'),(354,'edvzcsqgbv7215ih3rgl9qad','新界馬鞍山九十二區馬鞍山綜合運動場第一期建造工程 (合約編號：RE G324)','2025-06-03 01:59:31.072000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.352000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.624000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','新界馬鞍山九十二區馬鞍山綜合運動場第一期建造工程','建築署','1998 年 01 月 01 日 - 1999 年 08 月 27 日','<p>運動場包括跑道及足球場，總地盤面積約 42,000平方米。</p><br/><p>建造鋼筋混凝土看臺和鋼結構頂篷及鋼製覆蓋板。 打樁地基面積約長130米x 闊22 米，由頂篷最高點到地面約16.8米。</p><br/><p>第一期體育場館包括完成一個運動場和看臺。</p><br/><p>土壤，地表和地下排水。</p><br/><p>外部工程及附屬建築物。</p><br/><p>屋宇裝備安裝。</p><br/><br/><p>停車場，花槽，緊急車輛通道，鋪砌行人路面，圍牆，排水工程。</p>'),(355,'zji6pb0lsag64293fej2jzj9','道爾頓幼稚園改建及加建工程','2025-06-02 08:42:13.215000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.387000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.658000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','道爾頓幼稚園改建及加建工程','道爾頓基金有限公司','2016 年 12 月 18 日 - 2017 年 06 月 16 日','<p>香港道爾頓學校是一所非營利性雙語幼兒園和小學學校（國語，英語），將傳統中國文化的智慧與享譽世界的道爾頓教育計劃結合。學校的目的是提供一個快樂的環境，以培養孩子的好奇心；對自己的才智和成功能力建立自信；利用他們的自然語言能力；並教育他們成為快樂，負責任和獨立的學習者和思想家。</p><p>這個項目涉及拆除現有的隔斷牆，安裝新的隔斷牆，幹牆和玻璃隔斷，按照圖紙和法規要求完成各樓層的木門，玻璃門，油漆工，全新乙烯基地板和電機工作安裝等。由於項目施工期短和需要獲得學校批准許可證方可施工，所以這個項目工程於施工期間是非常緊張的。</p>'),(356,'wnqxx804g8nyncvn3jrxrehp','合约编号NL/2020/01东涌新市镇扩展 - 社区联络中心','2025-06-02 07:36:49.946000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.410000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.689000',8,36,'zh-CN','合约编号NL/2020/01东涌新市镇扩展 - 社区联络中心','土木工程拓展署','2020 年 12 月 31 日 - 2021 年 07 月 07 日','<p>工程的目的是改造现时总建筑楼面面积 (CFA) 约3,000平方米，2层高的工地办公室，成为一个建筑群，以容纳可持续大屿办事处 (SLO) 的卫星办公室及其顾问项目办公室、土木工程拓展署项目的展览和展示廊，及为当区人士及公众提供可作为社区联络的公众聚会、会议及活动空间，使他们可以与政府官员联系及沟通。</p><br/><p>将富有新特色的中庭空间引入现有工地办公大楼，通过拆除部份楼板和一楼楼层区域的相关支撑结构，三侧以一条新的走廊环绕，走廊设有玻璃栏杆，可通往新的大堂楼梯，作为公共活动的多功能空间。通过拆除现有斜屋顶的一部分，在上方建造新的天窗设计，保持原有的支撑结构完整。亦采用结构加固工程，确保现有建筑的穏定性。另外，对两个楼层的内部空间进行重新分区和翻新，以提供新的办公空间和其辅助设施。这个项目要根据建筑布局实施屋宇装备装置，室内和半室外景观特色要在指定位置进行。</p>'),(357,'r0jjrqjit93la8c2dtpwmhep','合約編號SS G511 在柴灣歌連臣角道興建骨灰安置所設施工程','2025-06-02 08:38:03.175000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.432000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.698000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','合約編號SS G511 在柴灣歌連臣角道興建骨灰安置所設施工程','建築署','2018 年 11 月 29 日 - 2023 年 08 月 31 日','<p>為配合香港人口老化而不斷增加的火化需求，政府計劃於2022年前在歌連臣角道興建一座設有25,000個龕位的骨灰龕，以及行人通道及道路擴建，作為在18區發展公共骨灰龕設施政策的一部分。</p><p>本項目包括興建一幢樓高五層、設有約25,000個龕位的大樓，以及公用香座、環保焚香設施、客運升降機、行政辦公室和數碼資訊站等配套設施。此外，本項目還包括興建一條連接歌連臣角道和新廈街的行人通道(設有自動扶梯和樓梯)，以及歌連臣角道的道路擴闊和改善工程。</p><br/><br/>'),(358,'j5514umkixmt813lq7jptb47','西营盘梅芳街10-22号和葵香街15-19号香港大学学生宿舍','2025-06-02 08:22:24.982000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.579000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.753000',8,36,'zh-CN','西营盘梅芳街10-22号和葵香街15-19号香港大学学生宿舍','香港大学','2019 年 04 月 02 日 - 2022 年 06 月 30 日','<p>2018年7月，立法会财务委员会批准一次性拨款，成立高等教育发展基金，为6所面对宿位短缺的大学教育资助委员会(教资会)资助大学加快兴建学生宿舍，香港大学是其中之一。</p><p>此项目为香港大学兴建一幢多楼层大楼，提供约250个学生宿舍。宿舍设有2层共用洗手间及6间设在平台楼层以上的无障碍学生房间。宿舍设施包括公共区域、管理人员宿舍及平台花园，并在梅芳街休憩处提供新的临时流动公共厕所及相关排水设施。</p>'),(359,'c3hp0gfn6jbybyvleu5x1u0m','灣仔愛群道34號香港童軍總會工程','2025-06-02 09:07:23.480000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.573000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.043000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','灣仔愛群道34號香港童軍總會工程','香港童軍總會','2016 年 07 月 18 日 - 2018 年 10 月 16 日','<p>香港童軍總會於2018 年4月20日正式揭幕其百年紀念建築。正式名稱為&quot;香港童軍百年紀念建築&quot;，該建築是一幢21層高的建築，是從原先的5層樓的鄧肇堅樓重建而來。作為香港島的地區總部。高聳的結構標誌著童軍歷史不斷發展的重要里程碑。</p><p>香港童軍百年大廈採用了許多可持續建築設計，包括遮陽鰭，以減少樓梯和電梯大堂的能量滲透和自然通風。該建築可容納綜合訓練中心，航空訓練中心，表演藝術中心和美術館，以及後勤設施，例如童軍商店，童軍會員圖書館和多功能廳。</p><p>百年大廈的範圍包括已完成的鋼筋混凝土建築，將完成所有建築服務。香港童軍總會希望通過新大樓為該國的童軍培訓提供更好的場地和設施。</p>'),(360,'i8e9t2y0t9otm76elk9g50oo','水邊圍及馬田村防洪工程及新慶村和永寧圍有關改善渠道工程 (合約編號：DC/2000/12)','2025-06-03 01:56:12.133000','2025-07-07 07:17:29.649000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.190000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','水邊圍及馬田村防洪工程及新慶村和永寧圍有關改善渠道工程','渠務署','2001 年 12 月 20 日 - 2004 年 03 月 12 日','<p>工程主要包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>在水邊圍及馬田村建洪氾抽水站，並包括內部和外部裝飾以及相關的蓄洪池</li><li>在水邊圍建邊界牆包括圍欄和閘口</li><li>在馬田村建擋土牆包括圍欄和閘口</li><li>渠務工程，電纜管道及兩個抽水站相關的拉線井</li><li>在水邊圍及馬田村的園林綠化工程</li><li>在流浮山道十字路口排水道和近屏山近新慶村建矩形排水渠道</li><li>其他上述項目的輔助工程</li><li>鋪設永寧圍附近的建築排水渠</li><li>鋪設直徑 1200毫米的雙管式水道及相關的排水口和特殊沙井</li></ul>'),(361,'lmdmbo7mcxhr75mi86wqonc1','落馬洲過關邊界第一期 - 收費亭擴建及其它設施','2025-06-03 01:56:56.050000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.300000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.564000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','落馬洲過關邊界第一期 - 收費亭擴建及其它設施','建築署','1999 年 03 月 01 日 - 1999 年 12 月 31 日','<p>這是一項快速工程。於落馬洲興建一大型過境交通平臺。合約包括設計和建造地基系統、過境站、鋼結構牌樓及其他配合設施。</p><br/><p>繁忙的過境交通，爲儘快完成本專案帶來沈重的壓力。我司爲加速完成任務，作出重大努力，與各有關單位衷誠合作，終於得以最短的時間完成本專案。</p><br/><p>另一方面，在施工期間，儘量避免影響已經相當繁忙的過境交通，也帶來一定程度的挑戰。</p>'),(362,'gk2jahyrusgye13j98iagkbq','重建位于中半山波老道20 号的港岛中学','2025-06-02 08:34:14.125000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.451000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.639000',8,36,'zh-CN','重建位于中半山波老道20 号的港岛中学','英基学校协会','2018 年 12 月 14 日 - 2022 年 08 月 10 日','<p>英基港岛中学是一所建于1974年的国际中学。面对教学空间不足、石屎剥落、钢筋锈蚀，以及其他结构性问题，英基建议重建老化的校舍。教育局根据现有情况及英基改善教学环境的计划，原则上同意英基的建议。</p><p>重建工程包括兴建一座8层高的新校舍，设有42个课室。新校舍内将设有四间小组教学室、七间实验室、八间特别室、一个图书馆、一个室内游泳池、行政办公室及设有音响效果媲美音乐厅的礼堂。</p>'),(363,'sp6pg81n1qvcmlylfp5f45r9','沙田污水處理廠第三期擴建第二部份工程 (合約編號：DC/2001/01)','2025-06-03 01:54:23.754000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.491000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.650000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','沙田污水處理廠第三期擴建第二部份工程','渠務署','2002 年 03 月 08 日 - 2005 年 10 月 18 日','<p>主要工程包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造六個初級沉澱缸及相關之初級污水泵房，占地五千零六十平方米</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造六個曝氣池及與其相關之兩個污水出/入口控制室，占地約七千六百九十米</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造一個深度約八米之排水泵房</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造十二個終級沉澱缸，共佔地七千一百五十米</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造一個平面面積約四百五十米的回流污泥泵房，二個砂礫分類裝置，二個引水溝渠及充氣砂礫溝渠</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造沙井，管道，溝渠，線坑、線井，浮渣井，雨水渠，氣喉及處理廠內的道路</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>四百支一米直徑，深度約三十至五十余米(至石層)之現澆攪拌樁及八百七十八支直徑二百一十九毫米，深度約二十五至四十米(至石層)之迷你樁</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>鋪設由二百毫米至一千六百毫米直徑之各類型管道，其中包括鋼管，熟鐵喉管及預製鋼筋混凝土喉管等，總長度約一千五百米</li></ul>'),(364,'dpqs0fcp5azy38x7bnzxt4ak','香港理工大學-設計及建造合約連接第八期校舍的行人天橋計劃','2025-06-02 09:26:05.553000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.453000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.664000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港理工大學-設計及建造合約連接第八期校舍的行人天橋計劃','香港理工大學','2015 年 06 月 15 日 - 2019 年 08 月 29 日','<p>工程主要包括設計和建造連接香港理工大學主校園和第八期校舍的行人天橋。</p><p>主跨度為68米的鋼管弓弦結構行人天橋位於漆咸道南。行人道整個寬度約7米而其附屬結構由高拉鋼懸掛在兩個主拱樑上。此行人天橋的美學是根據“飛魚”概念設計，與周圍的標誌性建築互相呼應。</p><p>工程項目包括設計及建造樁地基，樁帽，鋼筋混凝土升降機井結構，安裝升降機，鋼質行人天橋結構及其相關的附屬結構，裝飾及飾面，樓宇設備，涉及現有的Z座八期的交替及附加的工程的行人天橋連接工程。</p>'),(365,'cjmrs7yd2ntfe1opsf0ptneu','昂坪汙水處理廠，污水幹渠及污水排放管道 (合約編號： DC/2003/01)','2025-06-03 01:53:28.958000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.396000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.674000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','昂坪汙水處理廠，污水幹渠及污水排放管道','渠務署','2003 年 08 月 18 日 - 2006 年 03 月 09 日','<p>前往工地的通道一直爲整個專案的最大挑戰。由於限制車輛使用東涌道，本專案取得的許可證甚少。同時，因最接近工地的混凝土廠也需要超過一小時的車程，所以，每天混凝土的澆注量，只能限於200立方米。這限制對於工程的進度起了很大的影響。</p><br/><p>汙水處理廠內的各座鋼筋混凝土結構及建築物，都呈不規則的形狀。因此，雖耍採用特別設計的模板及複雜的臨時支撜結構。這也爲整個專案帶來一定的難度。</p>'),(366,'mcaj0kesuh4a7xozbcun9z3k','香港墨爾文國際學校興建工程','2025-06-02 08:41:30.884000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.461000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.735000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港墨爾文國際學校興建工程','香港墨爾文國際學校','2017 年 01 月 27 日 - 2018 年 08 月 24 日','<p>像香港這樣的國際城市，重要的是要有一個蓬勃發展的國際學校部門，以滿足該城市龐大且不斷增長的全球社區的需求。由於香港土地供應短缺，因此，政府在促進國際學校部門發展方面發揮了促進作用，並開展了學校分配工作。根據這項政策，香港墨爾文學院（MCHK）被授予了綠地，毗鄰香港科學園和風景秀麗的吐露港，這是一個非常優越的地理位置。該校舍的建設於2015年5月獲得香港特別行政區教育局的批准，於2018年8月開放。該校舍為來自不同文化和教育背景的中小學生提供960個名額。。</p><p>墨爾文學院佔地258,000平方英尺，7層樓擁有最先進的校園，其中包括學術，體育和休閒場所，融合了最新創新技術在教學，學習和環境可持續發展方面。該建築項目的主要範圍包括一個25m的室內溫水游泳池，AstroTurf Skypitch，450個座位的禮堂，一個開放式圖書館，七個科學實驗室，一個多功能室內體育館，音樂室和一個餐廳 。此外，提供美麗的美化環境，頂部屋頂以及外部運動場。</p><p>香港墨爾文國際學校提供了一個愉快而寬敞的學習環境。</p>'),(367,'atkmm7re6frff22o12ce7h2u','香港中文大學-神學院興建新聖堂大樓','2025-06-02 10:04:34.968000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.521000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.878000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港中文大學-神學院興建新聖堂大樓','香港中文大學','2009 年 10 月 02 日 - 2011 年 12 月 09 日','<p>中文大學籌劃興建的新聖堂為學生提供更良好的環境進行崇拜靈修生活。</p><p>集團於2009年獲得興建新聖堂大樓的工程。工程主要包括建造一個新教堂，面積一千四百五十平方米，可容納三百五十人。新教堂的主要特色是具有東方設計概念的綠色琉璃瓦頂，與四周的樹木互相襯托。圓形設計的聖堂則在四周裝上玻璃窗，能有效採入自然光，節省能源之餘亦可以欣賞窗外景色。教堂還設有十四塊彩繪玻璃和十二根柱子，每根都有象徵使徒的標記。</p>'),(368,'omfvvjmlh33o7ydl6arjlbb4','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works (AA Contract 304)','2025-06-03 02:13:26.937000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.556000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.872000',8,36,'en','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','01 September 1997 - 31 December 1999','<p>The contract to build the concourse extension, eleven fixed link bridges and 100,000ft². of apron area was awarded to the joint venture between Zen Pacific and Shui On. The project presented a number of challenges, not least the construction of the steel roof. The roof has a particularly complex geometry as the Northwest Concourse branches out from the main building at a 45-degree angle, which gives rise to grids of parallelograms with no right angles. A bolted design was chosen for the roof instead of the welded method used on the main terminal. The method of construction was chosen because it was more economical given the small number of roof modules involved and it improved installation time significantly. In addition, the method addressed the Airport Authority’s concerns over sparks from welding, which might have interfered with the airport’s operation.</p>'),(369,'oze4nvklzf3v3suqu2tszwrq','葵涌大白田街興建一所18間課室的小學 (合約編號 : SS R323)','2025-06-03 01:14:31.105000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.539000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.994000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','葵涌大白田街興建一所18間課室的小學','建築署','2007 年 04 月 30 日 - 2009 年 07 月 31 日','<p>合約包括建造一所樓高10層的小學校舍，內有18間課室及1座樓高39.50米的禮堂與及地基工程，排水工程，外部工程及其他相關設施。該小學大樓樓面面積約8,550平方米。葵涌大白田街兴建一所18间课室的小学</p>'),(370,'zkjyjf8jbi8yyvzltz2d0c6h','港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池重置工程 (沙田至中環綫 – 合約編號1126)','2025-06-02 09:36:25.190000','2025-07-07 07:17:30.754000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.138000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池重置工程','香港鐵路有限公司','2014 年 01 月 20 日 - 2017 年 05 月 31 日','<p>沙田至中環綫是香港鐵路有限公司在九龍及港島區進行的長達17公里的鐵路擴建工程。 該項目涉及將鐵路由大圍延伸至紅磡及由紅磡延伸至金鐘段，中間連接多條現有鐵路路線。</p><p>由於沙中綫會展站設於舊有灣仔碼頭公共運輸交匯處、港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池的地底，而會展站須以明挖回填方式興建，舊有港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池需永久重置於南面停車場的位置。舊有設施會在新設施建成並投入服務後才拆卸。</p><p>工程項目包括興建一座新的港灣道體育館及灣仔游泳池，建築物是一座有鋼桁架屋頂的5層高鋼筋混凝土樓房。工程還包括設計和建造大廈的外牆、內部結構和裝修、設備和裝置、屋宇裝備工程，其中包括起重橫樑和支撐細節，鋼結構通道平台，電氣，低壓電，過濾器，交流電，電梯，升降機和自動扶梯，煤氣, 水管和排水系統。</p>'),(371,'wwbbbdh29igqrj1pkg54p9ff','大埔林村農場項目','2025-06-02 07:39:56.865000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.195000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.352000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','大埔林村農場項目','香港城市大學','2020 年 12 月 14 日 - 2022 年 02 月 26 日','<p>城大購入一幅位於大埔林村、佔地逾一萬方米的農地興建農場，並飼養二十多頭牛隻作為動物醫學及生命科學院作教學用途。</p><br/><p>本項目工程包括興建 13 座建築物，包括成牛牛舍、幼牛牛舍、主樓大廈、更衣室區、看管員宿舍區、機器倉庫區、飼料中心區、變壓器和發電機房區、消防、灑水系統和泵房區、水箱和泵房區、儲物區、污水處理裝置區、微過濾裝置區、場地範圍的地下排水系統、地下水管、地下電纜引出坑、地下接地和避雷系統以及相關的機電系統，以及緊急車輛通道、圍欄、入口大門和綠化工程。</p>'),(372,'jatmi2wx8mmi27370ib6i6jv','新界马鞍山九十二区马鞍山综合运动场第一期建造工程 (合约编号：RE G324)','2025-06-03 01:45:10.653000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.237000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.399000',8,36,'zh-CN','新界马鞍山九十二区马鞍山综合运动场第一期建造工程','建筑署','1998 年 01 月 01 日 - 1999 年 08 月 27 日','<p>运动场包括跑道及足球场，总地盘面积约 42,000平方米。</p><br/><p>建造钢筋混凝土看台和钢结构顶篷及钢制覆盖板。打桩地基面积约长130米x 阔22 米，由顶篷最高点到地面约16.8米。</p><br/><p>第一期体育场馆包括完成一个运动场和看台。</p><br/><p>土壤，地表和地下排水。</p><br/><p>外部工程及附属建筑物。</p><br/><p>屋宇装备安装。</p><br/><p>停车场，花槽，紧急车辆通道，铺砌面，围墙，排水工程</p><br/><br/>'),(373,'pvajhpcgk24obij1pybbjgpt','Lantau and Airport Railway Kowloon South Tunnels and Ancillary Building (MTRC Contract No.503B)','2025-06-03 02:15:14.387000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.270000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.429000',8,36,'en','Lantau and Airport Railway Kowloon South Tunnels and Ancillary Building','Mass Transit Railway Corporation','01 November 1994 - 28 February 1998','<p>This project, which forms part of the overall scheme for the Lantau and Airport Railway Link between the Western Immersed Tube and the new Kowloon Station, involves the construction of plant buildings and tunnels.</p><br/><p>The project consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of diaphragm walls</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Large open cut excavation to construct the tunnel sections</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Bored piling works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Installation of floodgates and positioning of seawater intake/outfall p c units underwater</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated drainage and access roads</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Ancillary building</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Architectural; finishes and cladding</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>landscaping</li></ul>'),(374,'nhnmbohfzybp2qsuveiyghxy','大嶼山及機場鐵路九龍南隧道及輔助樓房 (合約編號：503B)','2025-06-03 02:03:53.695000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.233000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.447000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','大嶼山及機場鐵路九龍南隧道及輔助樓房','香港鐵路有限公司','1994 年 11 月 01 日 - 1998 年 02 月 28 日','<p>這工程是機場快線的其中一段，工程包括在西九沉管式隧道和新九龍站之間建造機房大樓及隧道。</p><br/><p>工程項目包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造截水牆</li><li>大型開挖作隧道興建</li><li>鑽孔樁工程</li><li>安裝防洪閘和在水底安裝海水引進 /出PC裝置</li><li>相關的渠務及路面配套</li><li>附屬建築物</li><li>裝飾面及面板</li><li>環境美化</li></ul>'),(375,'wwwy0kjkirkj4ybuccwln0xy','西營盤梅芳街10-22號和葵香街15-19號香港大學學生宿舍','2025-06-02 08:22:57.915000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.221000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.488000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','西營盤梅芳街10-22號和葵香街15-19號香港大學學生宿舍','香港大學','2019 年 04 月 02 日 - 2022 年 06 月 30 日','<p>2018年7月，立法會財務委員會批准一次性撥款，成立高等教育發展基金，為6所面對宿位短缺的大學教育資助委員會(教資會)資助大學加快興建學生宿舍，香港大學是其中之一。</p><p>此項目為香港大學興建一幢多樓層大樓，提供約250個學生宿舍。宿舍設有2層共用洗手間及6間設在平台樓層以上的無障礙學生房間。宿舍設施包括公共區域、管理人員宿舍及平台花園，並在梅芳街休憩處提供新的臨時流動公共廁所及相關排水設施。</p>'),(376,'rgksn8fhhx89ir62sm9s8f9t','合約編號NL/2020/01東涌新市鎮擴展 - 社區聯絡中心','2025-06-02 07:37:26.756000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.244000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.615000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','合約編號NL/2020/01東涌新市鎮擴展 - 社區聯絡中心','土木工程拓展署','2020 年 12 月 31 日 - 2021 年 07 月 07 日','<p>工程的目的是改造現時總建築樓面面積 (CFA) 約3,000平方米，2層高的工地辦公室，成為一個建築群，以容納可持續大嶼辦事處 (SLO) 的衞星辦公室及其顧問項目辦公室、土木工程拓展署項目的展覽和展示廊，及為當區人士及公眾提供可作為社區聯絡的公眾聚會、會議及活動空間，使他們可以與政府官員聯繫及溝通。</p><br/><p>將富有新特色的中庭空間引入現有工地辦公大樓，通過拆除部份樓板和一樓樓層區域的相關支撐結構，三側以一條新的走廊環繞，走廊設有玻璃欄杆，可通往新的大堂樓梯，作為公共活動的多功能空間。通過拆除現有斜屋頂的一部分，在上方建造新的天窗設計，保持原有的支撐結構完整。亦採用結構加固工程，確保現有建築的穏定性。另外，對兩個樓層的內部空間進行重新分區和翻新，以提供新的辦公空間和其輔助設施。這個項目要根據建築佈局實施屋宇裝備裝置，室內和半室外景觀特色要在指定位置進行。</p>'),(377,'n0bqrdlr8wgbaon8slj2rjn9','新中场范围检查大楼 (合约 P531)','2025-06-02 09:55:27.833000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.281000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.733000',8,36,'zh-CN','新中场范围检查大楼','香港机场管理局','2011 年 07 月 19 日 - 2012 年 09 月 03 日','<p>为提升香港国际机场处理旅客及货物运输的能力，香港机场管理局发表中场范围发展计划，希望加强香港在世界上的航运竞争力，使香港国际机场继续为国际及亚洲的区域航空中心。</p><p>集团于2011年获得中场范围发展计划其中一个配套工程，合约为一项设计及建造工程，项目范围包括新中场范围检查大楼的设计，供应，建造，测试和试运。</p>'),(378,'i9l1gtb61zlyvgl3k4znaoh6','香港科技大學逸夫演藝中心建設工程','2025-06-02 08:14:19.590000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.394000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.792000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','香港科技大學逸夫演藝中心建設工程','香港科技大學','2019 年 09 月 09 日 - 2020 年 11 月 08 日','<p>全新的逸夫演藝中心旨在成為香港科技大學的地標，舉辦大型活動，包括講座、音樂會、展覽和典禮，在校園內營造活力的文化氛圍，豐富學生、教職員和校友的生活和學習體驗。這座多功能會堂具有出色的環保設計，包括節能系統、可飲用水和沖廁系統的雙水箱設計，以及提升室內空氣質量等特點。</p><p>本工程項目涉及在西貢科大南邊入口附近建造一座樓高3層且能容納1300人的演藝中心。建造工程包括地基工程、建造鋼筋混凝土結構、圍護結構以及其他樓宇工程。由於施工在校園內進行，為減低施工期間對大學活動的影響，我們採取了嚴格和頻密的噪音及空氣質素管制措施。</p>'),(379,'lertqjjqqxy0og3atsb5s9vi','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai (Contract No. DC/2000/12)','2025-06-03 02:11:13.907000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.395000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.929000',8,36,'en','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai','Drainage Services Department','20 December 2001 - 12 March 2004','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen Floodwater Pumping Station on raft foundation including internal and external finishes and their associated floodwater storage ponds</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Boundary wall at Shui Pin Wai including fencing and gates</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Retaining walls at Ma Tin Tsuen including fencing and gates</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Drainage works, cable ducts and drawpits associated with the two pumping stations</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works at Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Cross road drain at Lau Fau Shan Road and rectangular drainage channels near San Hing Tsuen, Ping Shan</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Other ancillary works associated with items above</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of drainage channels near Wing Ning Wai</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of the twin 1200mm diameter pipes and the associated outfall and special manhole</li></ul>'),(380,'to5e09w2hdoetoypsmapi4hz','Expansion of Kiosks and other Facilities at Lok Ma Chau Boundary Crossing, Phase I','2025-06-03 02:11:53.115000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.966000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.371000',8,36,'en','Expansion of Kiosks and other Facilities at Lok Ma Chau Boundary Crossing, Phase I','Architectural Services Department, HKSAR','01 March 1999 - 31 December 1999','<p>This is a fast track project for the construction of a large podium at Lok Ma Chau for the cross border traffic. The project included the design and construction of piled foundation systems and the podium, kiosks, structural steel roof canopies and the other associated facilities.</p><br/><p>The extremely busy cross border traffic has bring along immence pressures to the rapid completion of the project. In order to complete the project in the shortest possible time, the Group has deployed huge amount of resources and affort, worked with close co-operations with all concerned parties. Finally, the project was completed on time.</p><br/><p>On the other hands, to mitigate any impact on the extremely busy cross border traffic during the construction was another major challenge</p>'),(381,'x962jaynxxvet1mjlna01mcb','湾仔爱群道34号香港童军总会工程','2025-06-02 09:09:23.415000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.880000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.381000',8,36,'zh-CN','湾仔爱群道34号香港童军总会工程','香港童军总会','2016 年 07 月 18 日 - 2018 年 10 月 16 日','<p>香港童军总会于2018 年4月20日正式揭幕其百年纪念建筑。正式名称为&quot;香港童军百年纪念建筑&quot;，该建筑是一幢21层高的建筑，是从原先的5层楼的邓肇坚楼重建而来。作为香港岛的地区总部。高耸的结构标志着童军历史不断发展的重要里程碑。</p><p>香港童军百年大厦采用了许多可持续建筑设计，包括遮阳鳍，以减少楼梯和电梯大堂的能量渗透和自然通风。该建筑可容纳综合训练中心，航空训练中心，表演艺术中心和美术馆，以及后勤设施，例如童军商店，童军会员图书馆和多功能厅。</p><p>百年大厦的范围包括已完成的钢筋混凝土建筑，将完成所有建筑服务。香港童军总会希望通过新大楼为该国的童军培训提供更好的场地和设施。</p>'),(382,'j0i9j7ckjb7doavokplmp2dw','把荔枝角公園游泳池的副池改建為室內暖水池 (合約編號 AL W316)','2025-06-02 09:57:23.054000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.249000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.467000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','把荔枝角公園游泳池的副池改建為室內暖水池','建築署','2010 年 02 月 01 日 - 2012 年 03 月 31 日','<p>政府計劃在荔枝角公園游泳池擬建室內暖水游泳設施，措施將有效向該區居民推廣冬季游泳可強身健體的訊息， 並提高該游泳池的整體使用率。</p><p>工程包括為副池設置一個輕型遮蓋及可伸縮邊牆及一個新的熱水系統；為有蓋行人道提供暖風系統；拆除位於副池毗鄰的現有兒童嬉水池和進行更衣室的通風/暖氣設施和熱水系統的相關改善工程。</p>'),(383,'xvjg8epm7rnzki88zcbgy9z1','Completion of Ma On Shan Sports Complex, Phase I at Area 92, Ma On Shan, N.T. (Contract No. RE G324)','2025-06-03 02:12:43.753000','2025-07-07 07:17:31.922000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.477000',8,36,'en','Completion of Ma On Shan Sports Complex, Phase I at Area 92, Ma On Shan, N.T.','Architectural Services Department Government of HKSAR','01 January 1998 - 27 August 1999','<p>A sports field, total site area approx. 42,000 m2 comprising running track, football field.</p><br/><p>Spectator stand with reinforced concrete structure and structural steel canopy with steel sheet cladding and piling foundations approx. 130m x 22m overall on plan and 16.8m high from ground level to the top of steel canopy.</p><br/><p>Completion of a partially completed sports complex comprising a sports field and a spectator stand.</p><br/><p>Soil, surface at er and sub-soil drainage.</p><br/><p>External works and ancillary buildings.</p><br/><p>Building services installation.</p><br/><p>Car park, planter, Emergency Vehicular Access (EVA), paving, fence wall, drainage works</p>'),(384,'vp6ufxd1hnyfmdabajtf7772','聖保祿醫院重建項目工程 建造A座新地庫，A座，B座及地庫D改建及加建工程','2025-06-02 08:38:39.160000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.355000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.540000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','聖保祿醫院重建項目工程 建造A座新地庫，A座，B座及地庫D改建及加建工程','法國沙爾德聖保祿女修會(香港)','2017 年 10 月 10 日 - 2024 年 09 月 25 日','<p>聖保祿醫院於1898年由法國沙爾德聖保祿女修會創立。醫院位於銅鑼灣核心地帶，是一所私立全科醫院，提供約500張病床，涵蓋20多個部門，並持續進行擴展設施及提供多元化服務。</p><p>本項目包括興建新地庫及擴建A 座、A、B座及地庫D的改建及加建工程、將現有露天停車場改建為園景花園、東院路道路擴闊及鋪路工程，以及拆除現有舊樓並建造新地庫結構及上層結構工程。</p><br/><br/>'),(385,'hzoc81svsmes8h8yiwbjlp7w','Village Flood Protection Works for Tai Kiu and Shui Pin Tsuen (Contract No. DC/2003/08)','2025-06-02 11:41:04.368000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.338000','2025-07-07 07:17:33.028000',8,36,'en','Village Flood Protection Works for Tai Kiu and Shui Pin Tsuen','Drainage Services Department','20 September 2004 - 22 July 2006','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><p>The Tai Kiu Floodwater Pumping Station and Power Supply Building and raft foundation and associated floodwater storage pond</p><p>Flow diversion chamber, underground fuel storage chamber, boundary wall at Tai Kiu</p><p>The Shui Pui Tsuen Floodwater Pumping Station with underground floodwater storage tank on raft foundation</p><p>Discharging chamber, flow intercepting chamber, inlet chamaber and fencing wall at Shui Pin Tsuen</p><p>Drainage works associated with the two pumping stations</p><p>Tree transplantation and planting works for Tai Kiu and Shui Pin Tsuen</p>'),(386,'txjzncrcnnargiwk7gmw6jhy','香港墨尔文国际学校兴建工程','2025-06-02 08:45:33.256000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.413000','2025-07-07 07:17:33.075000',8,36,'zh-CN','香港墨尔文国际学校兴建工程','香港墨尔文国际学校','2017 年 01 月 27 日 - 2018 年 08 月 24 日','<p>像香港这样的国际城市，重要的是要有一个蓬勃发展的国际学校部门，以满足该城市庞大且不断增长的全球社区的需求。由于香港土地供应短缺，因此，政府在促进国际学校部门发展方面发挥了促进作用，并开展了学校分配工作。根据这项政策，香港墨尔文学院（MCHK）被授予了绿地，毗邻香港科学园和风景秀丽的吐露港，这是一个非常优越的地理位置。该校舍的建设于2015年5月获得香港特别行政区教育局的批准，于2018年8月开放。该校舍为来自不同文化和教育背景的中小学生提供960个名额。 。</p><p>墨尔文学院占地258,000平方英尺，7层楼拥有最先进的校园，其中包括学术，体育和休闲场所，融合了最新创新技术在教学，学习和环境可持续发展方面。该建筑项目的主要范围包括一个25m的室内温水游泳池，AstroTurf Skypitch，450个座位的礼堂，一个开放式图书馆，七个科学实验室，一个多功能室内体育馆，音乐室和一个餐厅 。此外，提供美丽的美化环境，顶部屋顶以及外部运动场。</p><p>香港墨尔文国际学校提供了一个愉快而宽敞的学习环境。</p>'),(387,'yf77291dbhtx6x8vacmuexyz','合約編號SS J502 漁農自然護理署動物管理及動物福利綜合大樓的建造工程','2025-06-02 07:47:49.524000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.488000','2025-07-07 07:17:33.417000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','合約編號SS J502 漁農自然護理署動物管理及動物福利綜合大樓的建造工程','建築署','2020 年 09 月 21 日 - 2024 年 02 月 29 日','<p>由漁農自然護理署(漁護署)管理的動物管理及動物福利綜合大樓擁有約270個動物暫住設施，容量是土瓜灣舊址的兩倍多。該大樓擁有更妥善的檢疫措施，以縮短進口動物的等待時間。</p><p>本項目旨在興建一幢15層高的動物管理及動物福利綜合大樓(總高度約70米)，建築面積約21,300平方米，以重置漁護署各部門所需的營運和輔助設施，包括根據《狂犬病條例》(第421章)為進口動物設立的法定檢疫中心、圖書館、課室、展覽區、動物領養設施以促進動物福祉、實驗室設施、辦公室、員工設施、儲存空間、停車場區域、裝卸區及其他附屬設施。</p>'),(388,'mc8r3p1pjyp75hhc0j8qlz73','葵涌大白田街兴建一所18间课室的小学 (合约编号 : SS R323)','2025-06-03 01:25:46.323000','2025-07-07 07:17:33.027000','2025-07-07 07:17:33.508000',8,36,'zh-CN','葵涌大白田街兴建一所18间课室的小学','建筑署','2007 年 04 月 30 日 - 2009 年 07 月 31 日','<p>合约包括建造一所楼高10层的小学校舍，内有18间课室及1座楼高39.50米的礼堂与及地基工程，排水工程，外部工程及其它相关设施。该小学大楼楼面面积约8,550平方米。</p>'),(389,'vnolfer96ydoj0v95g2pmmz6','渔农自然护理署新界南动物管理中心及沙田植物检疫站重置工程 (沙田至中环线建造合约编号1113)','2025-06-02 09:46:45.310000','2025-07-07 07:17:32.553000','2025-07-07 07:17:33.522000',8,36,'zh-CN','渔农自然护理署新界南动物管理中心及沙田植物检疫站重置工程','香港铁路有限公司','2012 年 09 月 10 日 - 2013 年 11 月 29 日','<p>沙中线是政府建议兴建的其中一条策略性铁路，该路线沿途将会兴建一系列车站。其中